	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yeah, I've noticed this in eq.&nbsp;&nbsp;It's not a drastic boost, as in Quake II (fixed in Quake III, tho).<br><br>However, I've chalked the aid in do'n this more to AI pathing, than to the meager speed increase.  In Blackburrow, for example, if you're under the stool (at the bottom of the ramp to the elite ledge) and u strafe to the right a couple of feet, over the very samll bump, you'll see a drastic example of inefficient AI pathing:  the gnoll will run to the other side of the mesa, along the bump, then cross the bump, then run back down to the length of the bump back to you.  One might be able to bard dot a whole train this way, strolling back and forth across the bump.<br><br>Anyway, while solo'n my first 24 lvl's, I did a lot of running in perspective view.  After a while, u get a sence for which corners u can cut for which the mob will take a longer-squared-off-always-in-the-center-of-the-hall path.<br><br>...just my 2cp, :)<br><br>Cassiusdreuyhd, 36 lvl druid, the rathe<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
