	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 25th 12:25 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.40]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Maybe I'm missing it, but many posts tell you that you should be twisting several songs, but I don't see any telling you how.&nbsp;&nbsp;I guess most people feel it is obvious.  But for those who don't know, I'll tell you.  You need to hot key the songs.  I personally keep hot key table 1 as a general table, with no songs imbedded in it.  I use table 2 for my bard attack keys.  this is just because the keys I want to use depend upon whether I'm soloing or grouping, and upon the makeup of my group.  In this section, the first three keys are songs.  This lets me hit the 1, 2 and 3 keys on my keyboard and twist the three songs I place in these spots (generally a battle song, the heal song and one other song depending upon the makeup of the group).  The fourth number is my attack button.  the fifth is my persona button (lets me switch instruments and weapons quickly) and the sixth varies between a /assist button or the selos song (actually when I program this, I put it in the 4th slot), depending upon the group.  If you are trying to twist your songs using your mouse, you are just going to get frustrated.  Set up these hot keys and then hit the 1, 2 and 3 keys to sing your song.  You will be amazed how easy it is.  Any bard who doesn't use his hot keys to twist will ultimately be considered a badly played bard.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
