<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96695697731196></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96695697731196><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96695697731196>General Tips for under 20 Bards</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96695697731196#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=374><span id=Sage>Sapper</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>25 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Aug 22nd 11:09 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.88]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In case you havent read ANY other posts here or at any other sites, I'll tell you one more time...<br>LEARN TO TWIST!!<br>I watched a 17 level bard a few weeks back, in the throne room in CB, I asked him what he was singing.&nbsp;&nbsp;He said Whistling Warsong.<br>Can you be any more dense?[p]<br>You should always be singing at least 2 songs in combat, three is the standard that you should aspire to achieve, 4 for those with high real life dexterity and great connections.<br>What you sing depends on three things, its a judgment call from there.<br><b>*</b>The First Consideration is your Party. Consider your party makeup.  Tank heavy?  Caster Heavy?  Do you have an Enchanter? Do you have a Cleric?  Tanks like the Buff songs (Anthem De arms, Heal, Guardian Rythms, the occasional Jig) if they have alot of Procing wpns, break out the old drums and sing Chant of Battle, it will boost dex and str.<br>Casters like you to be able to taunt Mobs off them, and you need to be ready to tank for them.  Heal, Whistling warsong, Anthem or Chant is fine.  If you feel froggy, and if the environment allows, use your COD, DDD, and Largos to really taunt the enemy.<br>But do NOT use those AOE songs if you have multiple pulls and an enchanter with you.  Your AOE songs (Except Largos) will break Mez, and you will be wasting the Enchanter's Mana, and making him useless.<br><b>*</b>The second consideration is the target.  What is the nature of your enemy?  Caster?  Then sing Elemental, or Purifying and Guardian rythms.  (Ele and Pur rythms dont stack with each other, but either will stack with Guardian).  Also, consider using the Lullaby to break thier casts, it may not mez, but it WILL break a casters concentration regularly.  Is your target a part of an organized community?  Will it run for help, or will help come to it fairly quickly?  If so, have Selo's on standby and use it to allow the Tanks to keep up with it and kill it, or to run like hell if daddy or mommy shows up to git you.<br>Are you fighting one Mob or Multiples?  Your AOE songs (if you dont have an enchanter) can be of great use against multiple mobs, but prepare to be aggroed on, a LOT ;o)<br><b>*</b>The third consideration is your environment.  How close are the other mobs?  AOE or no AOE?  Do you need SOW?(Indoor Dungeons)  How far away is the puller pulling from, and how far away is the zone?  Where does the nearest Ubermob spwan, (Dvinn, Griffin, HG, Avoket, Named Orc or Gnoll)<br>You want to be aware at all times what is going on around you.  At the mid teens, you have songs that will help out the party in nearly every environment, and every situation, but having them memmed and knowing when to sing them is all part of what makes the difference between good Barding and Bad.<br><b>*</b>Bottom line, Dont sing a self buff song in a group unless you are the primary tank.  Never EVER bellow in a group unless you are trying to kill a running mob, there is something better you can do than 11 damage a mob every once in while, trust me.  <br>You are a party animal, sing songs to help the group, not yourself.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Sapper Diesalot, At Deaths Door.&nbsp;&nbsp;"Chuck Berry cant twist this good!"</td></tr>
