	   <tr><td colspan=2>The key to this post is that unlike most spell casters, our songs improve with age.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>Something to think about, however.  At higher levels, I've found it more usefull to sing chant of battle than anthem of arms because the dex bump increases weapon procs.  This is particularly true when grouped with a shaman or 'chanter that can dump an attack speed buff on, or if you twist celerity with chant.<br><br>Keadaian Gixslayer, lvl 38 bard (deceased)<br>Offbeat, lvl 22 bard<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
