	   <tr><td colspan=2>at lower levels(basically around 12-16) i found it handy to keep two different sets of armor.&nbsp;&nbsp;one for tanking, and one for other times.  In full bronze, i found i could tank efficiently ewnough to not die to the dervs in NRo, so long as theres a nuker or two behind you(remember if you have a real tank, don't try it... your nowhere near the tank a warrior is). this way, in a pinch, you can act as a tank(another plus to this is that your songs will taunt like a whore if you have enough going), giving the casters enough time to blast the heck outta the mobs as you sit there with a defense song and the heal song going, so you dont die.<br><br>I always keep a dwarven ringmail tunic with me even now because it gives decent magic resist, and very few things do. a very nice thing to switch on that DRT, and then play a resist buff song while you fight them casters and they'll barely scorch ya.<br><br>on another note, go down to lguk and get some shin ASAP in your career. its fairly safe to get down there(especially while using speed song), and shin is pretty good(especially since it's free)<br>&nbsp;<br>~Silverblade<br><br>Kilien Thundersong, Bard of Bristlebane<br></td></tr>
