<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=96680098213065></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96680098213065><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96680098213065>Charm as Taunt</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=96680098213065#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=720><span id= >KraxusMaclir</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 20th 3:49 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A simple tip for the Bards of this world to employ in later levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;At level 27 and then again at Level 39 a Bard can aquire a song that allows us to temporarily charm a mob.<br><br>Heres how it goews.<br><br>When in a group and for whatever reason a mob is fixed on any one target (the warrior for dealing way too much damage or the cleric for healing the warrior who is nearly dead from dealing that damage, for example) and nothing that anyone else can do is taunting the mob off of that person the Bard can, surprisingly, step in and rule.<br><br>Its quite simple and may be againt common thought but all you need to do is successfully charm the mob that will not be taunted by the paladin, ranger etc etc.   Once succesfully charmed that mobs hate list is erased and, for the 15 seconds that the Bard charm lasts, that mob is YOUR pet.  This can allow the cleric to recover and heal or allow the fighter to back out of range or in extreme cases for the druid to pull off an evac.  When the charm breaks the mob is instantly aggroed on you and not the previous player (yeah I know its rough being a bard, but hey we dont just wear plate mail for the looks) and the rest of the group can then proceed with combat as normal and finish the mob.<br><br>I can now say that I have used this tactic more times than I can remember and quite simply put it saves lives.  Be sure, however, that when employing this tactic to keep the group aware of what is going on.  Theres nothing that will annoy a caster more than wasting mana on a mob that is currently bard charmed.<br><br>Thats all there is to it.<br><br>Kraxus Maclir - Roadrunner Extrodinaire<br>Shining Alliance<br>40th Bard<br><br>"Meep Meep"<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
